According to a statement by the ministry, he noted that a maritime line between the Egyptian port of Ain Sokhna and the Kenyan port of Mombasa will be launched by mid-2020.

He made the remarks at the Egyptian-Italian Economic Forum that is held under the auspices of Prime Minister Mostafa Madbouli and is organised by the Ministry of Supply and Internal Trade.Â 

He added that other maritime lines for boosting the Egyptian foreign trade will be launched to northern and western Africa, according to the statement. --EgyptNews--